<!-- FEATURES -->
<section id="features">
  <div style="text-align:center; max-width:1100px; margin:0 auto 3rem;">
    <div class="section-label">Why LATERALUS</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Everything you need.<br>Nothing you don't.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
      Built from the ground up with scientific computing, mathematical elegance,
      and developer experience as first-class concerns.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="features-grid">
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">⟶</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Pipeline Operators</div>
      <div class="feature-desc">|&gt; chains transform data naturally. |? handles none gracefully. |&gt;= mutates in place. No callback hell.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">🧬</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Result &amp; Option Types<span style="display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;background:rgba(0,212,255,.15);color:var(--cyan);padding:.15rem .45rem;border-radius:8px;margin-left:.4rem;vertical-align:middle;">v1.5</span></div>
      <div class="feature-desc">Result::Ok(v) / Result::Err(e) and Option::Some(v) / Option::None — explicit error handling without exceptions.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">🎯</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Match Expressions<span style="display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;background:rgba(0,212,255,.15);color:var(--cyan);padding:.15rem .45rem;border-radius:8px;margin-left:.4rem;vertical-align:middle;">v1.5</span></div>
      <div class="feature-desc">Match as expression with ADT destructuring, guard clauses, list/tuple patterns, OR patterns, and wildcard bindings.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">∑</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Mathematical Precision</div>
      <div class="feature-desc">Auto-promotion, matrix algebra, complex numbers, Newton-Raphson, automatic differentiation. Julia-inspired.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">⚗</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Scientific Computing</div>
      <div class="feature-desc">CODATA constants, ODE solvers, FFT, statistical distributions, interpolation, linear regression — built in.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">🔐</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Cryptography</div>
      <div class="feature-desc">SHA-256, BLAKE2b, AES-256-GCM, HMAC-SHA256, XOR cipher, and the proprietary LBE binary format.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">🧠</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Hindley-Milner Types<span style="display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;background:rgba(0,212,255,.15);color:var(--cyan);padding:.15rem .45rem;border-radius:8px;margin-left:.4rem;vertical-align:middle;">v1.5</span></div>
      <div class="feature-desc">Full HM type inference with Robinson unification, occurs check, constraint solving, and pattern-aware inference.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">📡</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Event System</div>
      <div class="feature-desc">emit, probe, and measure keywords make reactive programming and observability first-class citizens.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">⏳</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Async &amp; Concurrency<span style="display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;background:rgba(0,212,255,.15);color:var(--cyan);padding:.15rem .45rem;border-radius:8px;margin-left:.4rem;vertical-align:middle;">v1.6</span></div>
      <div class="feature-desc">async/await, nursery blocks, typed channels, select multiplexing, cancellation tokens, and async for loops.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">📦</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Package Manager<span style="display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;background:rgba(0,212,255,.15);color:var(--cyan);padding:.15rem .45rem;border-radius:8px;margin-left:.4rem;vertical-align:middle;">v1.7</span></div>
      <div class="feature-desc">lateralus.toml manifests, semver resolution, lock files, build profiles, workspaces, @cfg conditional compilation.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">🪄</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Metaprogramming<span style="display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;background:rgba(0,212,255,.15);color:var(--cyan);padding:.15rem .45rem;border-radius:8px;margin-left:.4rem;vertical-align:middle;">v1.8</span></div>
      <div class="feature-desc">Procedural macros, @derive(Debug, Eq, Clone, …), const fn, reflect!(Type), quote/unquote AST transforms, comptime blocks.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">�</span>
      <div class="feature-title">FFI &amp; Ecosystem<span style="display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;background:rgba(0,212,255,.15);color:var(--cyan);padding:.15rem .45rem;border-radius:8px;margin-left:.4rem;vertical-align:middle;">v1.9</span></div>
      <div class="feature-desc">C FFI bridge with ctypes, WASM and JavaScript targets, Jupyter kernel for interactive notebooks, 5-target compilation.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">�🔬</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Rich Diagnostics</div>
      <div class="feature-desc">Errors that explain what went wrong and suggest how to fix it. Context windows, error chains, DNA fingerprints.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">🚀</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Multi-Target<span style="display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;background:rgba(0,212,255,.15);color:var(--cyan);padding:.15rem .45rem;border-radius:8px;margin-left:.4rem;vertical-align:middle;">v1.9</span></div>
      <div class="feature-desc">Transpile to Python 3.10+, C99 (hosted or freestanding), JavaScript ES2022, WebAssembly (WAT), compile to .ltlc binary. Powers LateralusOS.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">⚡</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Comprehensions<span style="display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;background:rgba(0,212,255,.15);color:var(--cyan);padding:.15rem .45rem;border-radius:8px;margin-left:.4rem;vertical-align:middle;">v1.4</span></div>
      <div class="feature-desc">List, set, and map comprehensions with filters. Ternary expressions. Spread operator. Guard and where clauses.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <span class="feature-icon">♻</span>
      <div class="feature-title">Self-Hosting</div>
      <div class="feature-desc">The v2 compiler is being written in LATERALUS itself. Lexer, parser, and codegen bootstraps live in bootstrap/.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PIPELINE DEMO -->
<section id="pipeline">
  <div class="section-label">Core Concept</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Data flows. Naturally.</h2>
  <p class="section-sub" style="margin:0 auto 3rem;">
    The pipeline operator |&gt; passes a value into the next function.
    Chain transformations without intermediate variables or callback nesting.
  </p>
  <div class="pipeline-flow">
    <div class="pipe-step">[1…10]<div class="pipe-label">raw data</div></div>
    <div class="pipe-arrow">|&gt;</div>
    <div class="pipe-step">filter(even)<div class="pipe-label">select</div></div>
    <div class="pipe-arrow">|&gt;</div>
    <div class="pipe-step">map(x²)<div class="pipe-label">transform</div></div>
    <div class="pipe-arrow">|&gt;</div>
    <div class="pipe-step">reduce(+)<div class="pipe-label">aggregate</div></div>
    <div class="pipe-arrow">→</div>
    <div class="pipe-step" style="border-color:var(--primary);color:var(--primary);">220<div class="pipe-label">result</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
<section id="audiences" style="background:var(--surface);">
  <div style="text-align:center; max-width:1100px; margin:0 auto 3rem;">
