        Zero-dependency cryptographic primitives, binary encoding, data integrity verification,
        and pipeline-driven processing make LATERALUS ideal for security tooling and CTFs.
      </div>
      <ul class="audience-features">
        <li>SHA-256, SHA-512, BLAKE2b, MD5 hash functions</li>
        <li>HMAC-SHA256 message authentication</li>
        <li>AES-256-GCM symmetric encryption</li>
        <li>XOR cipher and base64 encoding/decoding</li>
        <li>LBE binary format with HMAC integrity</li>
        <li>Result::Err for explicit failure tracking</li>
        <li>probe/emit for intrusion detection patterns</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="audience-card eng">
      <span class="audience-icon">⚙️</span>
      <div class="audience-title">Software Engineers</div>
      <div class="audience-desc">
        Clean syntax, Rust-inspired type safety, pipeline-driven data flow, comprehensive tooling,
        metaprogramming, and a familiar function-first paradigm make LATERALUS productive from day one.
      </div>
      <ul class="audience-features">
        <li>Result/Option ADTs — no null pointer exceptions</li>
        <li>Hindley-Milner type inference — write less, catch more</li>
        <li>Procedural macros &amp; @derive — zero boilerplate</li>
        <li>async/await, nursery blocks, typed channels</li>
        <li>LSP + DAP servers for VS Code integration</li>
        <li>Formatter, linter, profiler, package manager built-in</li>
        <li>Python 3.10+ transpiler — deploy anywhere</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- EXAMPLES -->
<section id="examples">
  <div class="section-label">In Action</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">See LATERALUS work</h2>
  <p class="section-sub" style="margin:0 auto 2rem;">
    From hello world to neural networks — all the same clean syntax.
  </p>
  <div class="tabs">
    <button class="tab-btn active" onclick="switchTab('adts')">Result/Option</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" onclick="switchTab('pipelines')">Pipelines</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" onclick="switchTab('science')">Science</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" onclick="switchTab('matching')">Patterns</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" onclick="switchTab('crypto')">Crypto</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" onclick="switchTab('structs')">Structs</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" onclick="switchTab('macros')">Macros</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" onclick="switchTab('async')">Async</button>
  </div>

  <!-- ADTs (v1.5) -->
  <div id="tab-adts" class="tab-panel active">
    <div class="demo-block">
      <div class="code-titlebar"><div class="dot dot-r"></div><div class="dot dot-y"></div><div class="dot dot-g"></div><span class="code-filename">result_option.ltl</span></div>
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="cmt">// Result::Ok / Result::Err — explicit error handling</span>
<span class="kw">fn</span> <span class="fn">parse_port</span>(s: <span class="typ">str</span>) <span class="op">-&gt;</span> <span class="typ">Result</span>&lt;<span class="typ">int</span>, <span class="typ">str</span>&gt; {
  <span class="kw">if</span> s == <span class="str">"443"</span>  { <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="typ">Result</span><span class="op">::</span><span class="fn">Ok</span>(<span class="num">443</span>) }
  <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="typ">Result</span><span class="op">::</span><span class="fn">Err</span>(<span class="str">"invalid port: {s}"</span>)
}

<span class="cmt">// Option::Some / Option::None — nullable without null</span>
<span class="kw">fn</span> <span class="fn">find_user</span>(id: <span class="typ">int</span>) <span class="op">-&gt;</span> <span class="typ">Option</span>&lt;<span class="typ">str</span>&gt; {
  <span class="kw">if</span> id == <span class="num">1</span> { <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="typ">Option</span><span class="op">::</span><span class="fn">Some</span>(<span class="str">"root"</span>) }
  <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="typ">Option</span><span class="op">::</span><span class="fn">None</span>
}

<span class="cmt">// Destructure with match expression</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> msg = <span class="kw">match</span> <span class="fn">parse_port</span>(<span class="str">"443"</span>) {
  <span class="typ">Result</span><span class="op">::</span><span class="fn">Ok</span>(p) <span class="op">=&gt;</span> <span class="str">"connected on port {p}"</span>,
  <span class="typ">Result</span><span class="op">::</span><span class="fn">Err</span>(e) <span class="op">=&gt;</span> <span class="str">"failed: {e}"</span>,
}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="tab-pipelines" class="tab-panel">
    <div class="demo-block">
      <div class="code-titlebar"><div class="dot dot-r"></div><div class="dot dot-y"></div><div class="dot dot-g"></div><span class="code-filename">pipeline.ltl</span></div>
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="cmt">// Text analysis in one pipeline</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> analysis = raw_text
  <span class="op">|&gt;</span> <span class="fn">split</span>(<span class="str">" "</span>)
  <span class="op">|&gt;</span> <span class="fn">filter</span>((<span class="typ">w</span>) <span class="op">=&gt;</span> <span class="fn">len</span>(w) &gt; <span class="num">3</span>)
  <span class="op">|&gt;</span> <span class="fn">map</span>(<span class="fn">lower</span>)
  <span class="op">|&gt;</span> <span class="fn">sort</span>()
  <span class="op">|&gt;</span> <span class="fn">group_by</span>((<span class="typ">w</span>) <span class="op">=&gt;</span> w[<span class="num">0</span>])  <span class="cmt">// group by first letter</span>

<span class="cmt">// Optional pipeline — safe on None</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> result = user_input
  <span class="op">|?</span> <span class="fn">trim</span>()
  <span class="op">|?</span> <span class="fn">parse_int</span>()
  <span class="op">|?</span> <span class="fn">validate_range</span>(<span class="num">0</span>, <span class="num">100</span>)
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="tab-science" class="tab-panel">
    <div class="demo-block">
      <div class="code-titlebar"><div class="dot dot-r"></div><div class="dot dot-y"></div><div class="dot dot-g"></div><span class="code-filename">physics.ltl</span></div>
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="kw">import</span> <span class="str">"science"</span>

<span class="cmt">// CODATA constants built in</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> lambda = PLANCK / (ELECTRON_MASS * v)  <span class="cmt">// de Broglie</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> E_rest  = ELECTRON_MASS * SPEED_OF_LIGHT ** <span class="num">2</span>

<span class="cmt">// ODE solver — exponential decay</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> solution = <span class="fn">solve_ode</span>(
  (<span class="typ">t</span>, <span class="typ">y</span>) <span class="op">=&gt;</span> -<span class="num">0.5</span> * y,
  <span class="num">1.0</span>, <span class="num">0</span>, <span class="num">10</span>, <span class="num">1000</span>
)

<span class="cmt">// FFT on signal</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> spectrum = signal <span class="op">|&gt;</span> <span class="fn">fft</span>() <span class="op">|&gt;</span> <span class="fn">power_spectrum</span>()
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="tab-matching" class="tab-panel">
    <div class="demo-block">
      <div class="code-titlebar"><div class="dot dot-r"></div><div class="dot dot-y"></div><div class="dot dot-g"></div><span class="code-filename">match.ltl</span></div>
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="kw">fn</span> <span class="fn">classify_particle</span>(mass: <span class="typ">float</span>, charge: <span class="typ">int</span>) <span class="op">-&gt;</span> <span class="typ">str</span> {
  <span class="kw">match</span> { mass, charge } {
    { mass <span class="kw">if</span> mass &lt; <span class="num">1e-30</span>, <span class="num">0</span>  } <span class="op">=&gt;</span> <span class="str">"neutrino"</span>,
    { mass <span class="kw">if</span> mass &lt; <span class="num">1e-30</span>, _ }  <span class="op">=&gt;</span> <span class="str">"lepton"</span>,
    { _,                     <span class="num">1</span>  } <span class="op">=&gt;</span> <span class="str">"proton"</span>,
    { _,                     <span class="num">-1</span> } <span class="op">=&gt;</span> <span class="str">"antiproton"</span>,
    { _,                     <span class="num">0</span>  } <span class="op">=&gt;</span> <span class="str">"neutron"</span>,
    _                              <span class="op">=&gt;</span> <span class="str">"unknown"</span>,
  }
}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="tab-crypto" class="tab-panel">
    <div class="demo-block">
      <div class="code-titlebar"><div class="dot dot-r"></div><div class="dot dot-y"></div><div class="dot dot-g"></div><span class="code-filename">crypto.ltl</span></div>
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="cmt">// Hashing</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> digest = <span class="fn">sha256</span>(<span class="str">"LATERALUS"</span>)
<span class="kw">let</span> fast    = <span class="fn">blake2b</span>(data, digest_size=<span class="num">32</span>)

<span class="cmt">// HMAC authentication</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> token = <span class="fn">hmac_sha256</span>(secret_key, message)
<span class="kw">let</span> valid = <span class="fn">hmac_verify</span>(secret_key, message, token)

<span class="cmt">// LBE — LATERALUS Binary Encoding</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> encoded = <span class="fn">lbe_encode</span>({ <span class="str">"user"</span>: <span class="str">"alice"</span>, <span class="str">"role"</span>: <span class="str">"admin"</span> })
<span class="kw">let</span> decoded = <span class="fn">lbe_decode</span>(encoded)
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="tab-structs" class="tab-panel">
    <div class="demo-block">
      <div class="code-titlebar"><div class="dot dot-r"></div><div class="dot dot-y"></div><div class="dot dot-g"></div><span class="code-filename">structs.ltl</span></div>
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="kw">struct</span> <span class="typ">Vector3</span> { x: <span class="typ">float</span>, y: <span class="typ">float</span>, z: <span class="typ">float</span> }
<span class="kw">struct</span> <span class="typ">Particle</span> {
  position: <span class="typ">Vector3</span>,
  velocity: <span class="typ">Vector3</span>,
  mass:     <span class="typ">float</span>,
  charge:   <span class="typ">float</span>,
}

<span class="kw">fn</span> <span class="fn">kinetic_energy</span>(p: <span class="typ">Particle</span>) <span class="op">-&gt;</span> <span class="typ">float</span> {
  <span class="kw">let</span> v2 = p.velocity.x**<span class="num">2</span> + p.velocity.y**<span class="num">2</span> + p.velocity.z**<span class="num">2</span>
  <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="num">0.5</span> * p.mass * v2
}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="tab-macros" class="tab-panel">
    <div class="demo-block">
      <div class="code-titlebar"><div class="dot dot-r"></div><div class="dot dot-y"></div><div class="dot dot-g"></div><span class="code-filename">metaprogramming.ltl</span></div>
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="cmt">// Procedural macros — expand at compile time</span>
<span class="kw">macro</span> <span class="fn">log!</span>(level, msg) {
  <span class="fn">println</span>(<span class="str">"[{level}] {msg}"</span>)
}

<span class="cmt">// @derive generates trait impls automatically</span>
<span class="kw">@derive</span>(<span class="typ">Debug</span>, <span class="typ">Eq</span>, <span class="typ">Clone</span>, <span class="typ">Serialize</span>)
<span class="kw">struct</span> <span class="typ">Config</span> { host: <span class="typ">str</span>, port: <span class="typ">int</span> }

<span class="cmt">// const fn — compile-time evaluation</span>
<span class="kw">const fn</span> <span class="fn">factorial</span>(n: <span class="typ">int</span>) <span class="op">-&gt;</span> <span class="typ">int</span> {
  <span class="kw">if</span> n &lt;= <span class="num">1</span> { <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="num">1</span> }
  <span class="kw">return</span> n * <span class="fn">factorial</span>(n - <span class="num">1</span>)
}

<span class="cmt">// Reflection — introspect types at compile time</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> info = <span class="fn">reflect!</span>(<span class="typ">Config</span>)
<span class="fn">println</span>(info.name)    <span class="cmt">// "Config"</span>
<span class="fn">println</span>(info.fields)  <span class="cmt">// ["host", "port"]</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="tab-async" class="tab-panel">
    <div class="demo-block">
      <div class="code-titlebar"><div class="dot dot-r"></div><div class="dot dot-y"></div><div class="dot dot-g"></div><span class="code-filename">concurrency.ltl</span></div>
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="cmt">// Typed channels for message passing</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> ch = <span class="fn">channel</span>&lt;<span class="typ">str</span>&gt;(<span class="num">10</span>)

<span class="cmt">// Structured concurrency with nursery blocks</span>
<span class="kw">nursery</span> workers {
  <span class="kw">spawn</span> <span class="fn">producer</span>(ch)
  <span class="kw">spawn</span> <span class="fn">consumer</span>(ch)
}  <span class="cmt">// all tasks complete before exiting</span>

<span class="cmt">// Select — multiplex across channels</span>
<span class="kw">select</span> {
  msg <span class="kw">from</span> inbox  <span class="op">=&gt;</span> { <span class="fn">handle</span>(msg) },
  <span class="kw">after</span> <span class="num">1000</span>      <span class="op">=&gt;</span> { <span class="fn">timeout</span>() },
  _               <span class="op">=&gt;</span> { <span class="fn">idle</span>() },
}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ECOSYSTEM -->
<section id="ecosystem">
  <div class="section-label">The Ecosystem</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">A complete environment</h2>
  <p class="section-sub" style="margin:0 auto 3rem;">
    Every tool you need — from IDE support to package management — built to work together.
  </p>
  <div class="eco-grid">
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Compiler</div><div class="eco-name">lateralus</div><div class="eco-desc">Multi-target: Python transpiler, bytecode VM, IR emitter, type checker</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Type System</div><div class="eco-name">HM Inference</div><div class="eco-desc">Hindley-Milner with Robinson unification, constraint solving, pattern inference</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Formatter</div><div class="eco-name">ltlfmt</div><div class="eco-desc">Automatic code formatter with pipeline alignment</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Linter</div><div class="eco-name">ltllint</div><div class="eco-desc">Static analysis with 15+ rules and fix suggestions</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Packages</div><div class="eco-name">ltlpkg</div><div class="eco-desc">Project scaffolding and dependency management</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">LSP</div><div class="eco-name">lsp_server</div><div class="eco-desc">Language server with completions, hover, diagnostics</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Debugger</div><div class="eco-name">dap_server</div><div class="eco-desc">Debug Adapter Protocol for VS Code step-through debugging</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Profiler</div><div class="eco-name">ltlprof</div><div class="eco-desc">Performance analysis with measure blocks and phase tracking</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Markup</div><div class="eco-name">LTLML</div><div class="eco-desc">Documentation language with KaTeX math and code blocks</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Binary</div><div class="eco-name">.ltlc</div><div class="eco-desc">Proprietary compiled format with HMAC integrity verification</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Notebook</div><div class="eco-name">.ltlnb</div><div class="eco-desc">Jupyter-inspired notebooks with code, markdown, math, and LTLML cells</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Editor</div><div class="eco-name">VS Code Ext</div><div class="eco-desc">Syntax highlighting, 20+ snippets, ADT support, language config</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Backend</div><div class="eco-name">C99 Transpiler</div><div class="eco-desc">Hosted (libc) or freestanding (bare-metal) C99 output for LateralusOS</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Backend</div><div class="eco-name">JS / WASM</div><div class="eco-desc">JavaScript ES2022 transpiler (ESM/CJS/IIFE) and WebAssembly (WAT) compiler</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">FFI</div><div class="eco-name">C Bridge</div><div class="eco-desc">Call C libraries via ctypes — load_library, FFIFunction, FFIRegistry, memory utilities</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">Kernel</div><div class="eco-name">Jupyter</div><div class="eco-desc">Interactive notebooks with execute, autocomplete, inspect, and ipykernel integration</div></div>
    <div class="eco-card"><div class="eco-tag">OS</div><div class="eco-name">LateralusOS</div><div class="eco-desc">Bare-metal x86_64 OS with GUI desktop, terminal, VFS, 21 shell commands, networking</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- BLOG PREVIEW -->
<section id="blog" style="background:var(--surface);text-align:center;">
